    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-19T20:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-19T20:15:00-05:00" n="388"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d388">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/983: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="47" xml:id="d388fn47">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-20T09:15:00+08:00"
                            >September 20, 1937—9:15 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 20—7:30 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0020. Am advising Admiral Hasegawa that our naval vessels will remain Nanking as
                    long as any of our nationals are in the city and warning him to advise his
                    aviators accordingly.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
